The paper presents a probabilistic approach to generate a small, query-able summary of a dataset for interactive data exploration. This involves developing a theoretical framework and formulation of a probabilistic representation of the data that can be used to give approximate query answers. The paper also discusses solving techniques and critical optimizations to improve preprocessing time and query accuracy. Given this focus on probabilistic representation and query answering, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (Databases). However, the paper also involves machine learning techniques such as the Principle of Maximum Entropy, which suggests a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses optimization techniques and query processing, which could fit with cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
